I was watching "Wig," a 2019 documentary about drag queens, with my boyfriend and during one of the early montages his face furrowed in confusion – "Why are they playing Ukrainian music?"

It turned out that the filmmakers, in their pursuit of a gypsy-like vibe, filled the documentary with Ukrainian folk music. I guess to a North American viewer that soundtrack is exotic and mysterious, but it was hilarious to watch from a Ukrainian perspective – the music of babushkas and wheat fields playing overtop of drag queens in Brooklyn.
